A chemical plant explosion in Jilin Province caused a major water pollution incident in the Songhua River, affecting Harbin.
The responsible company, Jilin Petroleum and Chemical Company, is under scrutiny.
China and Russia are cooperating to address the pollution.
Measures have been taken to clean up the contaminated water, with a focus on ensuring safe drinking water.
The government is cracking down on polluting enterprises and implementing environmental protection measures.
The polluted water is gradually subsiding as efforts to mitigate the pollution continue.
Residents are advised to avoid using water from the polluted river.
